  4) primary key: 
        -> primary key is a most powerfull concept of sql constraint using of primary key we can make any column as 
           unique column but primary key we can apply only on single field of table.

           unique                                                   primary key
        -> many column                                            -> only one column
        -> can accept blank/null                                  -> not accept blank/null
             e.g.                                                    e.g.
        -> email,phone,adhar card etc...                          -> id,roll no,enroll-id,etc...

        creattion time:

        syntax:
            create table <tablename>
            (
                filedname <datatype> primary key
            );

            e.g.
            create tabel dummy
            (id int primary key,name varcahr(20));

             desc dummy;
            +-------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
            | Field | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra |
            +-------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
            | id    | int         | NO   | PRI | NULL    |       |
            | name  | varchar(20) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
            +-------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+

            insert into dummy
            values
            (1,'mustved'),
            (2,'aaaa');
            select * from dummy;
            +----+---------+
            | id | name    |
            +----+---------+
            |  1 | mustved |
            |  2 | aaaa    |
            +----+---------+

            insert into dummy 
            values
            (1,'bbbbb');
             Duplicate entry '1' for key 'dummy.PRIMARY'
            ERORR

        after creation:

        syntax:
            alter table <tablename> add primary key (filed name);

            e.g.

            alter table dummy add primary key (id);

        droping:
        alter table dummy drop primary key;
        +-------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
        | Field | Type        | Null | Key | Default | Extra |
        +-------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
        | id    | int         | NO   |     | NULL    |       |
        | name  | varchar(20) | YES  |     | NULL    |       |
        +-------+-------------+------+-----+---------+-------+
